{"title": "Snarl of the Beast", "description": "Carroll John Daly, enormously popular in his day but has since faded into obscurity, is often credited with penning the first hard-boiled crime story in 1922 and creating the first hard-boiled detective in 1923. The Snarl of the Beast is his popular gumshoe Race Williams' first full-length novel and features Daly's classic P. I. as fast-thinking, hard-nosed smart aleck who finds trouble at every turn and isn't afraid to sling some lead to get himself out of a tough spot. This story begins with Race being tailed and assaulted by a hulking beast of a man, only to be chased by cops when he's mistaken for the murderer of a sergeant he wasn't on the best of terms with. Can Williams track down the beast and stop him before anyone else dies? - Summary by Ben Tucker", "duration": 24629, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17644", "name": "Carroll John Daly"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/snarl_of_beast_bt_2306_librivox/snarl_beast_2306.jpg", "copyright_year": "1927", "genres": ["Detective Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Ben Tucker"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ben Tucker"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Verla Viera"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I. The Attack", "readers": [16758], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/snarl_of_beast_bt_2306_librivox/snarlofthebeast_01_daly_64kb.mp3", "duration": 819}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II. A Dead Police Officer", "readers": [16758], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/snarl_of_beast_bt_2306_librivox/snarlofthebeast_02_daly_64kb.mp3", "duration": 806}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III. The Police Are Curious", "readers": [16758], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/snarl_of_beast_bt_2306_librivox/snarlofthebeast_03_daly_64kb.mp3", "duration": 647}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV. Within The Tenement Room", "readers": [16758]